# Components and Styling

## Component Structure

- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Add `"use client"` directive when components use client-side features
- Name components using PascalCase
- Store components in `src/components/` directory
- Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility

## Component Organization

Components are organized by feature or type in `src/components/`:

**Feature-Based Directories:**
- `auth/` - Authentication components (LoginForm, AuthCheck, etc.)
- `FunctionLogs/` - Function logging UI components
- `Highlights/` - Highlight display and management components
- `integrations/` - Third-party integration components (Readwise, Airtable)
- `Layout/` - App layout components (Header, Sidebars, etc.)
- `ScheduledTasks/` - Scheduled task management components
- `Sidebar/` - Sidebar-specific components
- `SparkPreview/` - Spark preview panel components

**Type-Based Directories:**
- `icons/` - Custom icon components
- `Providers/` - React context providers
- `theme/` - Theme and dark mode components
- `ui/` - Reusable UI primitives (buttons, inputs, tables, etc.)

**Best Practices:**
- Each feature directory should have an `index.ts` file exporting all components
- Related components should be co-located in their feature directory
- Generic/reusable components go in `ui/`
- Feature-specific components go in their respective feature directory

## Styling with Tailwind

- Use Tailwind CSS for styling components
- Use Tailwind for common UI components (buttons, inputs, etc.)
- Do not use Radix or Shadcn components

## Icons

- Prefer `lucide-react` for icons
- Name icon components using PascalCase
- Place custom icons in `src/components/icons`

## Component Example

```tsx
// src/components/UserProfile.tsx
"use client";

import { User } from "@/lib/types";
import { UserCircle } from "lucide-react";

interface UserProfileProps {
  user: User;
  onEdit?: () => void;
}

export function UserProfile({ user, onEdit }: UserProfileProps) {
  return (
    <div className="p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
      <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
        <UserCircle className="w-10 h-10 text-gray-700" />
        <div>
          <h3 className="font-medium">{user.name}</h3>
          <p className="text-sm text-gray-500">{user.email}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      {onEdit && (
        <button 
          onClick={onEdit}
          className="mt-4 px-3 py-1 text-sm bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700"
        >
          Edit Profile
        </button>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Toast Notifications

- Use `react-toastify` for toast notifications
- Implement in client components only
- Use provided methods: `toast.success()`, `toast.error()`, etc. 